description.p:
In accordance with a first aspect of the present invention, a shape detection method comprises:
retrieving a plurality of sets of partial measurement data, each set defining a corresponding part of the surface of a circular measured object in a sequence about the object, each set of partial measurement data being determined by a displacement detector positioned, for each set of the partial measurement data, at a corresponding reference position;
setting a reference position of a first set of the partial measurement data as a measurement reference position;
combining the plural sets of partial measurement data, each adjusted by adding thereto the difference between the measurement reference position and the reference position corresponding to that partial measurement data set, in sequence into one combined data set so that the combined data set is defined with respect to the measurement reference position; and
calculating the shape of the surface of the measured object using the combined data set.

In accordance with a second aspect of the invention, a shape detection device for a shape measuring apparatus comprises:
a retriever configured to retrieve a plurality of sets of partial measurement data, each set defining a corresponding part of the surface of a circular measured object in a sequence about the object, each set of partial measurement data being determined by a displacement detector positioned, for each set of the partial measurement data, at a corresponding reference position;
a setter configured to set a reference position of a first set of the partial measurement data as a measurement reference position;
a combiner configured to combine the plural sets of partial measurement data, each adjusted by adding thereto the difference between the measurement reference position and the reference position corresponding to that partial measurement data sequence, in sequence into one combined data set so that the one combined data set is defined with respect to the measurement reference position, and
a calculator configured to calculate the shape of the surface of the measured object using the combined data set.

